%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAkshaye%20Khanna%20is%20gaining%20praise%20for%20his%20role%20in%20%E2%80%98Chhaava%E2%80%99.%20Despite%20his%20current%20accolades%2C%20he%20once%20opened%20up%20about%20the%20emotional%20impact%20of%20going%20bald%20at%20a%20young%20age.%20He%20compared%20it%20to%20a%20pianist%20losing%20his%20fingers%2C%20highlighting%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20actors%20in%20maintaining%20their%20appearance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fwhen-akshaye-khanna-reacted-to-his-premature-balding-its-heartbreaking-and-it-can-mentally-kill-you%2Farticleshow%2F118558690.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20The%20Church%20Of%20England%20Refuses%20To%20Learn%20From%20Its%20Abuse%20Scandals%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIt%20nearly%20played%20out%20as%20expected.%20Despite%20pleas%20from%20victims%20for%20a%20fully%20independent%20body%20to%20oversee%20safeguarding%20in%20the%20Church%20of%20England%2C%20the%20General%20Synod%20(its%20national%20assembly)%20last%20week%20opted%20for%20a%20compromise%E2%80%94enhancing%20oversight%20but%20stopping%20short%20of%20complete%20independence.%20Members%20of%20the%20Church's%20parliament%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20new%20measures%20to%20handle%20abuse%20complaints%2C%20a%20move%20aimed%20at%20rebuilding%20trust%20after%20multiple%20scandals.%20But%20for%20survivors%20who%20have%20long%20called%20for%20real%20accountability%2C%20the%20decision%20will%20likely%20feel%20like%20yet%20another%20case%20of%20the%20Church%20protecting%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20five-day%20Synod%20meeting%20unfolded%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20an%20unprecedented%20crisis%20for%20the%20Church%20of%20England.%20The%20abuse%20scandals%20have%20deepened%20an%20already%20severe%20loss%20of%20public%20confidence%2C%20compounding%20multiple%20crises%20that%20threaten%20the%20Church's%20future.%20For%20centuries%2C%20it%20has%20presented%20itself%20as%20Britain's%20moral%20compass%E2%80%94but%20its%20failure%20to%20protect%20vulnerable%20individuals%20has%20shattered%20that%20image.%20To%20many%2C%20the%20Church's%20actions%20reek%20of%20hypocrisy%2C%20especially%20given%20its%20firm%20stance%20on%20issues%2C%20such%20as%20sexuality%20and%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EYears%20Of%20Silence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20the%20Archbishop%20of%20Canterbury%2C%20Justin%20Welby%20(the%20Church's%20senior%20most%20figure)%2C%20stepped%20down%20amid%20a%20damning%20report%20that%20found%20that%20he%20failed%20to%20act%20on%20allegations%20of%20child%20sexual%20abuse%20within%20the%20Church%20of%20England.%20The%20independent%20inquiry%20into%20the%20late%20John%20Smyth%2C%20a%20barrister%20and%20evangelical%20leader%2C%20exposed%20decades%20of%20unchecked%20abuse%20of%20over%20130%20boys%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20Africa.%20The%20report%20stated%20that%20Welby%20%26quot%3Bcould%20and%20should%26quot%3B%20have%20formally%20reported%20the%20abuse%20when%20he%20first%20became%20aware%20in%202013%2C%20but%20instead%2C%20Church%20leaders%20displayed%20a%20%26quot%3Black%20of%20curiosity%26quot%3B%20and%20allowed%20the%20matter%20to%20be%20minimised.%20Smyth%20was%20able%20to%20continue%20his%20alleged%20abuse%20due%20to%20systemic%20failures%20within%20the%20Church%2C%20which%20ignored%20warnings%20as%20far%20back%20as%201982.%20The%20scandal%20has%20deeply%20damaged%20the%20Church's%20moral%20authority%2C%20with%20an%20NGO%2C%20The%20Children's%20Society%2C%20even%20refusing%20a%20donation%20from%20Welby%2C%20citing%20its%20inconsistency%20with%20their%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Welby's%20resignation%2C%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20Church%20of%20England%20has%20been%20trying%20hard%20to%20regain%20public%20trust.%20Efforts%20are%20on%20to%20find%20a%20successor.%20The%20Church's%20responsibilities%20have%20been%20divided%20by%20some%20key%20insiders.%20The%20process%20of%20appointing%20a%20new%20Archbishop%20is%20expected%20to%20take%20months.%20It%20could%20be%20a%20challenging%20job%20as%20the%20next%20Archbishop%20will%20inherit%20a%20Church%20struggling%20with%20a%20credibility%20crisis%2C%20declining%20membership%20and%20growing%20divisions%20over%20social%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Religion%20As%20Cloak'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20high-profile%20cases%20of%20abuse%20involved%20Bishop%20Peter%20Ball%2C%20who%20was%20sentenced%20to%20prison%20for%20a%20series%20of%20offences%20against%20teenage%20boys%20and%20young%20men.%20The%20court%20was%20told%20that%20Ball%20used%20%26quot%3Breligion%20as%20a%20cloak%26quot%3B%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20abuse%20between%20the%201970s%20and%201990s.%20What%20was%20shocking%20was%20that%20Bishop%20Ball%20had%20received%20support%20from%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Royal%20Family%20and%20other%20establishment%20figures%20as%20he%20attempted%20to%20evade%20charges%20in%20the%20early%201990s%2C%20when%20allegations%20of%20sexual%20abuse%20against%20young%20aspiring%20priests%20first%20surfaced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20abuse%20allegations%20against%20high-profile%20church%20figures%2C%20such%20as%20John%20Smyth%2C%20are%20not%20an%20isolated%20case.%20For%20years%2C%20the%20Church%20of%20England%20has%20been%20rocked%20by%20multiple%20abuse%20scandals%2C%20with%20damning%20reports%20revealing%20systemic%20failures%20in%20handling%20cases%20of%20sexual%20abuse%2C%20which%20also%20involves%20children.%20The%20most%20significant%20investigation%20was%20the%20Independent%20Inquiry%20into%20Child%20Sexual%20Abuse%20(IICSA)%2C%20which%20in%202020%20exposed%20how%20Church%20leaders%20repeatedly%20prioritised%20protecting%20the%20institution's%20reputation%20over%20safeguarding%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20a%20few%20key%20findings%20from%20the%20Independent%20Inquiry%20into%20Child%20Sexual%20Abuse%20(IICSA)%202020%20regarding%20the%20Church%20of%20England%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFailure%20to%20Protect%20Victims%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Church%20of%20England%20prioritised%20its%20reputation%20over%20the%20safety%20of%20children%2C%20often%20shielding%20clergy%20accused%20of%20abuse%20instead%20of%20taking%20decisive%20action.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EInstitutional%20Cover-Ups%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Senior%20church%20figures%2C%20including%20bishops%2C%20were%20found%20to%20have%20ignored%20or%20downplayed%20allegations%2C%20allowing%20abusers%20to%20continue%20working%20within%20the%20Church.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EInadequate%20Safeguarding%20Measures%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Church's%20internal%20safeguarding%20systems%20were%20deeply%20flawed%2C%20with%20inconsistent%20reporting%20procedures%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20independent%20oversight.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EVictim-Blaming%20and%20Poor%20Support%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Survivors%20were%20often%20met%20with%20dismissal%2C%20scepticism%2C%20or%20hostility%2C%20exacerbating%20their%20trauma%20instead%20of%20offering%20them%20justice%20and%20pastoral%20care.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IICSA%20report%20concluded%20that%20the%20Church%20leadership%20had%20enabled%20a%20culture%20of%20secrecy%20and%20inaction.%20Even%20after%20public%20revelations%2C%20the%20Church's%20safeguarding%20policies%20remained%20inconsistent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20The%20Church%20Of%20England%20Matters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Church%20of%20England%20still%20matters%20in%20this%20country.%20Britain%20presents%20a%20constitutional%20paradox%3A%20it%20is%20a%20largely%20secular%20society%2C%20yet%20it%20has%20an%20official%20state%20religion.%20In%20contrast%2C%20India%20is%20a%20secular%20republic%20with%20no%20state%20religion.%20The%20Church%20of%20England%20holds%20a%20unique%20legal%20and%20constitutional%20status%2C%20despite%20the%20UK%20being%20a%20pluralistic%20nation%20where%20religious%20practice%20is%20in%20steep%20decline.%20Also%2C%20the%20Church%20and%20the%20State%20have%20a%20historic%20bond.%20Founded%20in%201534%20by%20King%20Henry%20VIII%20after%20breaking%20from%20the%20Roman%20Catholic%20Church%2C%20the%20Church%20of%20England%20has%20been%20intertwined%20with%20the%20British%20state%20from%20its%20inception.%20The%20monarch%E2%80%94now%20King%20Charles%20III%E2%80%94is%20not%20just%20the%20Head%20of%20State%20but%20also%20the%20Supreme%20Governor%20of%20the%20Church%20of%20England.%20At%20coronations%2C%20the%20monarch%20takes%20an%20oath%20to%20uphold%20the%20%26quot%3BProtestant%20Reformed%20Religion%26quot%3B%2C%20cementing%20the%20Church's%20place%20in%20state%20traditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELaw%20And%20Politics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20most%20secular%20democracies%2C%20the%20Church%20of%20England%20retains%20direct%20influence%20in%20Parliament.%20The%20House%20of%20Lords%20includes%2026%20bishops%20(called%20the%20'Lords%20Spiritual')%2C%20who%20can%20debate%20and%20vote%20on%20legislation.%20This%20grants%20the%20Church%20a%20formal%20role%20in%20lawmaking.%20The%20Archbishop%20of%20Canterbury%20plays%20a%20central%20role%20in%20state%20ceremonies%2C%20from%20royal%20weddings%20to%20Remembrance%20Day%2C%20reinforcing%20the%20Church's%20presence%20in%20national%20life.%20For%20many%2C%20the%20monarchy%20and%20the%20Church%20of%20England%20symbolise%20Britain's%20historical%20continuity.%20While%20secular%20campaigners%20push%20for%20disestablishment%2C%20there%20is%20little%20public%20demand%20for%20change.%20Even%20among%20non-religious%20Britons%2C%20the%20issue%20does%20not%20generate%20strong%20opposition.%20It%20must%20be%20added%20that%20the%20Church%20is%20like%20a%20soft%20power%20too%2C%20as%20one-third%20of%20state-funded%20schools%20in%20England%20are%20Church%20of%20England%20institutions.%20It%20remains%20a%20key%20player%20in%20social%20justice%2C%20engaging%20in%20issues%20like%20homelessness%20and%20asylum%20seeker%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Global%20Problem%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20must%20bear%20in%20mind%20that%20scandals%20within%20religious%20institutions%20are%20not%20confined%20to%20the%20Church%20of%20England.%20Across%20faiths%20and%20fraternities%2C%20allegations%20have%20surfaced%20in%20the%20Roman%20Catholic%20Church%2C%20Evangelical%20megachurches%2C%20Orthodox%20Jewish%20communities%2C%20and%20Islamic%20institutions.%20There%20appears%20to%20be%20common%20patterns%20of%20systemic%20cover-ups%2C%20a%20reluctance%20to%20hold%20perpetrators%20accountable%2C%20and%20a%20prioritisation%20of%20institutional%20reputation%20over%20victims.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Catholic%20Church's%20scandals%2C%20spanning%20many%20countries%2C%20remain%20the%20most%20notorious%2C%20with%20investigations%20exposing%20decades%20of%20hidden%20misconduct%20at%20the%20highest%20levels.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Evangelical%20and%20Protestant%20churches%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20US%2C%20have%20also%20faced%20serious%20allegations%20of%20abuse.%20Unlike%20the%20Church%20of%20England%2C%20which%20has%20a%20central%20authority%2C%20these%20religious%20institutions%20are%20often%20unable%20to%20act%20against%20abuse%20because%20of%20their%20decentralised%20structures%2C%20which%20make%20oversight%20difficult.%20Similarly%2C%20ultra-Orthodox%20Jewish%20communities%20have%20been%20criticised%20for%20discouraging%20victims%20from%20going%20to%20secular%20authorities.%20Abuse%20allegations%20in%20Islamic%20institutions%20often%20go%20under-reported%20due%20to%20cultural%20stigmas.%20In%20all%20these%20cases%2C%20institutions%20have%20been%20accused%20of%20shielding%20abusers%20rather%20than%20protecting%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20case%2C%20the%20lesson%20for%20the%20Church%20of%20England%20is%20clear.%20Both%20its%20well-wishers%20and%20critics%20agree%20that%20it%20must%20embrace%20transparency%2C%20hand%20oversight%20to%20an%20independent%20body%20and%20implement%20survivor-centred%20reforms.%20As%20a%20state%20institution%2C%20the%20Church%20of%20England%20has%20a%20unique%20responsibility%20to%20lead%20by%20example.%20Failure%20to%20act%20decisively%20will%20only%20deepen%20public%20scepticism%20not%20just%20towards%20itself%20but%20towards%20faith-based%20institutions%20in%20general.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740484920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fiu9h4sa_justin-welby-archbishop-of-canterbury-resigns-reuters_625x300_13_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-church-of-england-refuses-to-learn-from-its-abuse-scandals-7792154%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20November%2C%20the%20Archbishop%20of%20Canterbury%2C%20Justin%20Welby%20(the%20Church's%20senior%20most%20figure)%2C%20stepped%20down%20amid%20a%20damning%20report%20that%20found%20that%20he%20failed%20to%20act%20on%20allegations%20of%20child%20sexual%20abuse%20within%20the%20Church%20of%20England.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-church-of-england-refuses-to-learn-from-its-abuse-scandals-7792154%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Why%20No%20Death%20Penalty%20For%20Sajjan%20Kumar'%3A%201984%20Riots%20Victims'%20Families%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20families%20of%20victims%20of%20the%201984%20anti-Sikh%20riots%20have%20expressed%20huge%20disappointment%20over%20former%20Congress%20MP%20Sajjan%20Kumar%20%26quot%3Bgetting%20away%26quot%3B%20with%20a%20life%20sentence%20instead%20of%20death%20penalty%2C%20which%20the%20families%20have%20been%20demanding%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20local%20court%20in%20Delhi%20today%20awarded%20life%20sentence%20to%20Mr%20Kumar%20for%20killing%20a%20father%20and%20a%20son%20in%20Delhi's%20Saraswati%20Vihar%20on%20November%201%2C%201984%2C%20when%20the%20anti-Sikh%20riots%20began%20following%20the%20assassination%20of%20the%20then%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20by%20two%20bodyguards%20from%20the%20Sikh%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioners%20have%20the%20option%20of%20challenging%20the%20sentence%20in%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20special%20judge%20Kaveri%20Baweja%20announced%20the%20sentence%2C%20the%20families%20waiting%20outside%20the%20Delhi%20court%20broke%20out%20and%20shouted%20for%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%2080%20years%20old%20now%2C%20we%20have%20never%20got%20justice%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20elderly%20woman%20told%20NDTV.%20%26quot%3BChildren%20and%20women%20were%20murdered%20on%20the%20streets.%20I%20will%20never%20forget%20the%20horror%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20said%20the%20offences%20committed%20by%20Mr%20Kumar%20were%20undoubtedly%20brutal%20and%20reprehensible%2C%20but%20underscored%20certain%20mitigating%20factors%2C%20including%20his%20age%20of%2080%20years%20and%20illnesses%20that%20%26quot%3Bweigh%20in%20favour%20of%20imposing%20a%20lesser%20sentence%2C%20instead%20of%20death%20penalty%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20man%20who%20lost%20his%20family%20and%20relatives%20in%20the%20anti-Sikh%20riots%20told%20NDTV%20they%20are%20not%20at%20all%20happy%20with%20the%20sentence%20given%20to%20Mr%20Kumar%20as%20they%20wanted%20nothing%20less%20than%20the%20death%20penalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDefinitely%20we%20are%20not%20satisfied.%20Some%20186%20cases%20were%20opened%20and%20an%20SIT%20%5Bspecial%20investigation%20team%5D%20was%20formed.%20After%20the%20BJP%20came%20in%20the%20Centre%2C%20the%20justice%20system%20started%20moving%20fast%20though%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20%5Bthe%20case%5D%20was%20not%20politicised%20by%20others.%20The%20Congress%20only%20did%20that%20because%20it%20was%20a%20genocide.%20It%20was%20not%20a%20danga%20(riot)%2C%20it%20was%20a%20genocide%20like%20how%20Hitler's%20men%20killed%20people%2C%20the%20Congress's%20people%20killed%20Sikhs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIndira%20Gandhi's%20killers%20were%20given%20the%20death%20sentence%20fast.%20For%20one%20killing%2C%20justice%20came%20swiftly.%20For%20the%20murders%20of%2010%2C000%20people%2C%20we%20are%20still%20waiting%20for%20justice.%20It%20goes%20to%20show%20justice%20is%20different%20for%20the%20common%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2031%2C%20the%20local%20court%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20after%20hearing%20additional%20submissions%20by%20public%20prosecutor%20Manish%20Rawat%20in%20the%20case%20linked%20to%20the%20killing%20of%20Jaswant%20Singh%20and%20his%20son%20Tarundeep%20Singh%20during%20the%201984%20anti-Sikh%20riots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELawyer%20Anil%20Sharma%2C%20however%2C%20submitted%20Mr%20Kumar's%20name%20was%20not%20there%20from%20the%20very%20beginning%20and%20there%20was%20a%20delay%20of%2016%20years%20in%20naming%20him%20as%20an%20accused%20by%20the%20witness.%20It%20was%20also%20submitted%20that%20a%20case%20in%20which%20Mr%20Kumar%20was%20convicted%20by%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20was%20pending%20for%20appeal%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20public%20prosecutor%20objecting%20to%20Mr%20Sharma's%20submission%20said%20Mr%20Kumar%20was%20not%20known%20to%20the%20victims'%20family%2C%20and%20when%20they%20became%20aware%20of%20who%20Mr%20Kumar%20was%2C%20the%20complainant%20named%20him%20in%20her%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20lawyer%20HS%20Phoolka%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20riot%20victims%2C%20said%20the%20police%20investigations%20were%20manipulated%2C%20tardy%20and%20meant%20to%20save%20the%20accused.%20Mr%20Phoolka%20said%20the%20situation%20during%20the%20anti-Sikh%20riots%20was%20extraordinary%20and%20so%20these%20cases%20have%20to%20be%20dealt%20with%20in%20this%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Phoolka%20referred%20to%20a%20judgment%20of%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20and%20said%20it%20was%20not%20an%20isolated%20case%2C%20but%20a%20part%20of%20a%20bigger%20massacre.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740484800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fgq9m9hu8_sajjan-kumar_625x300_25_February_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fwant-nothing-less-than-death-penalty-1984-anti-sikh-riots-victims-families-on-sajjan-kumar-7792161%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20families%20of%20victims%20of%20the%201984%20anti-Sikh%20riots%20have%20expressed%20huge%20disappointment%20over%20former%20Congress%20MP%20Sajjan%20Kumar%20%26quot%3Bgetting%20away%26quot%3B%20with%20a%20life%20sentence%20instead%20of%20death%20penalty%2C%20which%20the%20families%20have%20been%20demanding%20for%20decades.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fwant-nothing-less-than-death-penalty-1984-anti-sikh-riots-victims-families-on-sajjan-kumar-7792161%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Charlamagne%20Tha%20God%2C%20iHeartMedia%20Announce%202025%20Black%20Effect%20Podcast%20Festival%20Lineup%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740484800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FCharlamagne-Tha-God.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236318997%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Radio%20host%2C%20podca