get%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egraduated%20care%20facility%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20older%20people%2C%20but%20Cori%20and%20I%20agreed%20they%20should%20stay%20in%20the%20house%20for%20as%20long%20as%20possible.%20We%20believed%20it%20would%20be%20better%20for%20them%20health-wise.%20We%20also%20knew%20that%20if%20we%20didn't%20stay%20close%20to%20them%20when%20we%20started%20having%20kids%2C%20they%20wouldn't%20see%20their%20grandkids%20very%20often%2C%20as%20we'd%20likely%20end%20up%20settling%20in%20another%20part%20of%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20right%20after%20we%20got%20married%2C%20Cori%20moved%20in%2C%20too%2C%20and%20we%20started%20taking%20care%20of%20Mom%20and%20Dad.%20Our%20house%20is%20a%20double-story%20building%20with%20five%20bedrooms%20and%20a%20den%2C%20so%20there%20was%20plenty%20of%20room%20for%20all%20of%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226c7d1b56-3e36-4335-b39e-7dcf460ec96e%5C%22%3EThere%20were%20plenty%20of%20benefits%20to%20living%20with%20my%20mom%20and%20dad%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMom%20and%20Dad%20shifted%20from%20the%20upstairs%20to%20the%20downstairs.%20It%20was%20easier%20for%20them%20not%20to%20have%20to%20walk%20up%20and%20down%20the%20stairs%20to%20get%20to%20their%20bedroom.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fliving-multigenerational-home-lessons-pateince-openness-death-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultigenerational%20living%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20had%20many%20positive%20aspects.%20When%20we%20welcomed%20our%20three%20sons%20and%20daughter%2C%20it%20meant%20that%20they%20spent%20plenty%20of%20quality%20time%20with%20our%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20folks%20were%20homebodies%2C%20so%20they%20didn't%20mind%20watching%20our%20kids%20or%20our%20pets.%20If%20we%20were%20running%20down%20to%20our%20trailer%20at%20Mt%20Baker%20and%20we%20asked%20them%20to%20watch%20the%20dogs%20for%20the%20weekend%2C%20it%20was%20never%20a%20problem.%20If%20we%20wanted%20to%20go%20out%20for%20dinner%20