2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fsounds%2Fplay%2Fm00289vf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20BBC's%20%26quot%3BDesert%20Island%20Discs%26quot%3B%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20Apple%20was%20struggling%20%E2%80%94%20it%20took%20a%20%24150%20million%20investment%20from%20rival%20Microsoft%20to%20help%20the%20company%20become%20profitable%20again.%20Apple%20needed%20a%20hit%20product%2C%20and%20Jobs%20enlisted%20a%20young%20Ive%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bimpossible%20task.%26quot%3B%20It%20was%20the%20world's%20first%20glimpse%20into%20Ive's%20vision%20for%20tech%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20started%20work%20from%20the%20first%20day%20that%20we%20met%20on%20what%20became%20the%20iMac%2C%26quot%3B%20Ive%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPersonal%20computers%20didn't%20yet%20have%20a%20role%20in%20most%20people's%20lives%20back%20then%2C%20and%20many%20were%20intimidated%20by%20them%2C%20he%20said.%20Their%20mission%2C%20to%20focus%20on%20making%20a%20product%20%26quot%3Bfor%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20became%20the%20philosophy%20that%20gave%20Apple%20an%20edge%20over%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221348%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22customers%20in%20front%20of%20iMac%20computers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bcabbbc040bd1b4ca2f583%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221011%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20colorful%20iMacs%20were%20designed%20to%20make%20PCs%20more%20accessible%20to%20consumers.%3Cp%3EYOSHIKAZU%20TSUNO%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIve%20put%20thought%20into%20each%20detail%20of%20the%20colorful%20lineup%20of%20PCs%20to%20make%20it%20more%20approachable%20for%20consumers.%20The%20handle%2C%20for%20example%2C%20was%20an%20intentional%20design%20choice%20to%20give%20the%20iMac%20a%20recognizable%20characteristic%20for%20those%20unfamiliar%20with%20the%20power%20of%20computing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20references%20im