ought-in-shop-app-talent-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacquired%20the%20team%20behind%20Swedish%20shopping%20startup%20Tictail%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20many%20of%20those%20leaders%20were%20key%20to%20the%20growth%20of%20its%20Shop%20app.%20It%20also%20acquired%20the%20B2B%20commerce%20marketplace%20Handshake%20in%202019%2C%20and%20those%20founders%20have%20gone%20on%20to%20hold%20product%20leadership%20roles%20at%20Shopify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShopify%20is%20also%20doubling%20down%20on%20AI%20talent%20in%20other%20ways.%20In%20August%2C%20the%20company%20hired%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmikhail-parakhin-shopify-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMikhail%20Parakhin%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20its%20new%20CTO.%20Parakhin%20led%20AI%20advancements%20like%20Copilot%20at%20Microsoft%20and%20also%20developed%20search%20engines%20and%20cloud%20services%20for%20more%20than%20four%20years%20as%20Yandex's%20CTO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoffmeister%20also%20said%20during%20the%20earnings%20call%20that%20Shopify%20would%20continue%20to%20make%20strategic%20investments%20in%20startups%20building%20tech%20that%20its%20merchants%20would%20find%20valuable.%20Its%202024%20investments%20included%20participation%20in%20a%20pre-seed%20round%20for%20Convergence%2C%20which%20is%20building%20an%20AI%20agent%20called%20Proxy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EGot%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amstone%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Emstone%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amlstone%40protonmail.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Emlstone%40protonmail.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20or%20on%20the%20secure%20messaging%20app%20Signal%20at%20%40mlstone.04.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshopify-boosts-ai-talent-acquisition-six-startup-acquihires-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740477602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bce0cf4e7cbbbe3dc4622f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshopify-boosts-ai-talent-acquisition-six-startup-acquihires-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shopify%20enhanced%20its%20AI%20talent%20pool%20through%20six%20startup%20acquihires%20in%20the%20last%20year.%20It's%20competing%20for%20talent%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bwhite-hot%26quot%3B%20market%20for%20AI.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mstone%40businessinsider.com%20(Madeline%20Stone)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A33%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshopify-boosts-ai-talent-acquisition-six-startup-acquihires-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Elon%20Musk%20hates%20OpenAI's%20for-profit%20transformation%20plan.%20He's%20not%20the%20only%20one.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227488%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Altman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67acfeaeeb4be2fff9a47271%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224994%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman.%3Cp%3EJOEL%20SAGET%20%2F%20AFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%2C%20which%20is%20owned%20by%20a%20non-profit%2C%20wants%20to%20adopt%20a%20more%20traditional%20corporate%20structure.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EElon%20Musk%2C%20Meta%2C%20charities%2C%20academics%2C%20and%20AI%20entrepreneurs%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20plan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20question%20OpenAI's%20legal%20process%2C%20and%20whether%20its%20non-profit%20will%20be%20compensated%20fairly.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-openai-ceo-career-net-worth-ycombinator-prepper-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20attempting%20a%20thorny%20maneuver%2C%20transforming%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-ai-adjusted-earnings-groupon-wework-accounting-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20a%20convoluted%20non-profit%20into%20a%20more%20conventional%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJungwon%20Byun%20knows%20what%20that's%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20organization%20that%20Byun%20cofounded%2C%20an%20AI%20lab%20named%20Ought%2C%20went%20through%20a%20similar%20transition.%20Launched%20in%202018%2C%20Ought%20built%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-frontier-crowded-winners-losers-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20research%20tools%2C%20and%20was%20structured%20as%20a%20non-profit%20because%20its%20cofounders%20didn't%20expect%20AI%20to%20be%20commercially%20viable%20any%20time%20soon%2C%20Byun%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%20Then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20launched%2C%20AI%20mania%20took%20hold%2C%20and%20the%20leadership%20team%20realized%20their%20structure%20might%20be%20a%20hindrance%20to%20raising%20capital%20and%20pursuing%20their%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20was%20made%20to%20spin%20out%20Ought's%20core%20product%2C%20Elicit%2C%20as%20a%20for-profit%20company%2C%20along%20with%20most%20of%20its%20staff.%20Byun%20and%20several%20other%20executives%20slated%20to%20lead%20the%20independent%20Elicit%20recused%20themselves%20from%20discussions%2C%20and%20a%20firm%20specializing%20in%20asset%20valuations%20was%20hired%20to%20independently%20appraise%20the%20value%20of%20Elicit%2C%20so%20the%20remaining%20non-profit%2C%20Ought%2C%20could%20be%20paid%20appropriately.%20(Byun%20declined%20to%20share%20the%20exact%20price%2C%20though%20she%20said%20Elicit%20chose%20to%20pay%20a%20premium%20on%20top%20of%20the%20recommended%20price.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20planned%20transformation%20is%20on%20a%20far%20grander%20scale%2C%20but%20faces%20similar%20questions%20and%20potentially%20more%20gnarly%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%20wants%20to%20extricate%20OpenAI's%20revenue-generating%20business%20from%20its%20non-profit%20parent%2C%20creating%20a%20more%20traditional%20company%20that%20can%20take%20in%20investments%20and%20give%20stock%20to%20shareholders%20who%20expect%20big%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20is%20complicated%20by%20OpenAI's%20complex%20corporate%20structure%2C%20the%20billions%20of%20dollars%20it%20has%20already%20raised%20from%20investors%2C%20and%20rival%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E's%20attempts%20to%20block%20the%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20Elon%20though.%20There's%20a%20growing%20chorus%20of%20critics%2C%20including%20entrepreneurs%2C%20other%20companies%20and%20charities%2C%20investors%2C%20academics%2C%20and%20activists%2C%20who%20say%20OpenAI%20may%20be%20about%20to%20make%20a%20grave%20mistake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByun%20is%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%20%26quot%3BArtificial%20general%20intelligence%20is%20the%20most%20transformative%20technology%20of%20our%20lifetime%20and%20OpenAI%20is%20absolutely%20at%20the%20frontier%20and%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20players%20in%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20think%20giving%20up%20governance%20rights%20to%20controlling%20the%20most%20important%20technology%20of%20our%20lifetime%20is%20an%20insanely%20huge%20decision%20and%20will%20affect%20all%20of%20humanity%20at%20a%20very%20great%20scale%20for%20a%20long%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20advice%20to%20OpenAI's%20charitable%20parent%20organization%3A%20Do%20not%20sell%20to%20anyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%2C%20obviously%2C%20the%20details%20of%20what%20pressures%20they're%20under%20and%20what%20the%20details%20are%20of%20the%20options%20they're%20considering%2C%20and%20how%20it%20affects%20the%20mission%2C%26quot%3B%20Byun%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20from%20what%20I%20can%20see%2C%20I%20absolutely%20would%20not%20sell%20those%20governance%20rights%20or%20give%20them%20up.%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20over%20the%20past%20week.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e72b62a3-8e0f-49ac-a674-afbb23ed5fb9%5C%22%3EA%20convoluted%20structure%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221006%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20chart%20showing%20OpenAI's%20structure%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b90270c040bd1b4ca2ded3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22719%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20chart%20showing%20OpenAI's%20structure.%3Cp%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20was%20established%20as%20a%20non-profit%20in%202015.%20Over%20time%2C%20its%20need%20for%20capital%20to%20pay%20for%20AI%20development%20prompted%20it%20to%20establish%20a%20for-profit%20subsidiary%20to%20raise%20venture%20funding%20and%20pursue%20business%20partnerships%20and%20revenue-generating%20products.%20This%20(and%20various%20other%20subsidiaries)%20are%20controlled%20by%20the%20nonprofit%2C%20which%20is%20controlled%20by%20a%20board%20of%20directors%20chaired%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbret-taylor-resignation-salesforce-marc-benioff-showdown-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBret%20Taylor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20alongside%20Altman%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstacart-ceo-robots-wont-replace-gig-workers-delivery-speed-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFidji%20Simo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Larry%20Summers%2C%20and%20other%20business%20luminaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20board's%20main%20legal%20obligation%20is%20to%20further%20the%20non-profit's%20charitable%20mission%2C%20which%20is%20to%20build%20%26quot%3Bsafe%20and%20beneficial%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20humanity%2C%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20delivering%20returns%20to%20shareholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20now%20seeks%20to%20transition%20to%20a%20more%20conventional%20corporate%20structure%2C%20turning%20the%20for-profit%20subsidiary%20into%20an%20independent%20public%20benefit%20company%20that%20controls%20%26quot%3BOpenAI's%20operations%20and%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPBCs%20are%20relatively%20common.%20This%20approach%20takes%20into%20account%20the%20interests%20of%20shareholders%2C%20other%20stakeholders%2C%20and%20the%20public.%20With%20investors%20taken%20care%20of%2C%20OpenAI%20has%20said%20this%20will%20help%20the%20startup%20raise%20%26quot%3Bnecessary%20capital%20with%20conventional%20terms%20like%20others%20in%20this%20space.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228bbba900-dc8c-4885-ba47-3f4014a6bea0%5C%22%3EFinding%20fair%20value%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67473802ede4eeae3929f769%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk%2C%20OpenAI%20cofounder%20turned%20bitter%20rival.%3Cp%3ELEON%20NEAL%2FPOOL%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20remaining%20non-profit%20will%20receive%20shares%20in%20the%20public%20benefit%20company%20%26quot%3Bat%20a%20fair%20valuation%20determined%20by%20independent%20financial%20advisors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20may%20be%20the%20ultimate%20challenge%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20one%20made%20more%20complex%20by%20potential%20conflicts%20of%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20investors%20and%20others%20focused%20on%20the%20startup's%20business-focused%20future%20may%20prefer%20to%20pay%20the%20non-profit%20less%20for%20its%20assets%20and%20control%2C%20leaving%20the%20new%20for-profit%20entity%20with%20more%20financial%20firepower.%20However%2C%20some%20of%20these%20people%20could%20be%20in%20positions%20to%20influence%20the%20valuation%20and%20decision-making%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElon%20Musk%2C%20an%20OpenAI%20cofounder%20who%20acrimoniously%20split%20from%20Altman%2C%20has%20sued%20the%20startup%20over%20its%20plans.%20Musk%20and%20a%20group%20of%20other%20investors%20also%20made%20a%20bid%20in%20February%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-elon-musk-97-billion-bid-openai-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacquire%20the%20nonprofit%20parent%20OpenAI%20Inc.%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%2497.4%20billion.%20That%20was%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20total%20value%20of%20the%20entire%20startup%2C%20based%20on%20its%20most-recent%20funding%20round.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20in%20the%20public's%20interest%20to%20ensure%20that%20OpenAI%2C%20Inc.%20is%20compensated%20at%20fair%20market%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Musk%20consortium%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BThat%20value%20cannot%20be%20determined%20by%20insiders%20negotiating%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20same%20table.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20board%20has%20an%20obligation%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20nonprofit%20is%20getting%20a%20fair%20value%20for%20giving%20up%20its%20assets%20and%20control%2C%20according%20to%20Ellen%20Aprill%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20charities%20at%20the%20UCLA%20School%20of%20Law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20very%20big%20issues%20is%20what%20is%20fair%20market%20value%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIn%20particular%2C%20how%20much%20should%20the%20nonprofit%20get%20for%20giving%20up%20control%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPart%20of%20what%20Musk%20and%20his%20group%20were%20trying%20to%20do%20with%20this%20offer%20is%20to%20set%20at%20least%20some%20floor%2C%20some%20sense%20of%20what%20the%20fair%20market%20value%20would%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BPutting%20it%20out%20for%20auction%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0let's%20see%20what%20people%20would%20pay.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c1ea6f61-9bef-46b2-af94-bbdb49c847e3%5C%22%3EShould%20Altman%20recuse%20himself%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Altman%20presenting%20onstage%20with%20the%20OpenAI%20logo%20behind%20him.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a256d95a8a7bf049196e7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222801%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman.%3Cp%3EJason%20Redmond%2FAFP%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETaylor%2C%20the%20OpenAI%20board%20chairman%2C%20officially%20rebuffed%20Musk.%20%26quot%3BOpenAI%20is%20not%20for%20sale%2C%20and%20the%20board%20has%20unanimously%20rejected%20Mr.%20Musk's%20latest%20attempt%20to%20disrupt%20his%20competition%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20wrote%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BAny%20potential%20reorganization%20of%20OpenAI%20will%20strengthen%20our%20nonprofit%20and%20its%20mission%20to%20ensure%20AGI%20benefits%20all%20of%20humanity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20days%20before%20that%2C%20Altman%20publicly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-elon-musk-97-billion-bid-openai-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshot%20the%20bid%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20post%20on%20X%20that%20mocked%20the%20struggles%20of%20the%20Musk-owned%20social%20network%3A%20%26quot%3Bno%20thank%20you%20but%20we%20will%20buy%20twitter%20for%20%249.74%20billion%20if%20you%20want.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman's%20post%20prompted%20some%20discussion%20of%20whether%20he%20was%2C%20or%20should%20be%2C%20recused%20from%20this%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20looking%20at%20a%20conflicted%20transaction%20like%20this%20one%2C%20it's%20much%20easier%20to%20satisfy%20the%20court's%20review%20if%20you%20take%20people%20who%20are%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20their%20transaction%20out%20of%20the%20negotiations%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Peter%20Molk%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20noted%20that%20under%20Delaware%20law%2C%20Altman%20isn't%20legally%20required%20to%20remove%20himself.%20Molk%20also%20cautioned%20against%20recusing%20too%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20value%20in%20his%20being%20there.%20Along%20the%20way%2C%20he%20can%20provide%20useful%20insight%20and%20information%20that's%20actually%20useful%20for%20OpenAI%2C%20for%20the%20nonprofit%2C%20if%20they're%20going%20to%20go%20ahead%20with%20that%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Molk%20explained.%20%26quot%3BYou%20want%20to%20try%20and%20strike%20a%20balance%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20do%20their%20job%2C%20that%20helps%20a%20transaction%20occur%20in%20a%20way%20that's%20actually%20beneficial%20to%20all%20parties%2C%20but%20then%20have%20them%20take%20themselves%20out%20of%20the%20picture%20once%20you're%20beyond%20that%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224d9628b2-afea-4734-a5e4-762d6c5c48c5%5C%22%3EMeta%20and%20others%20pile%20on%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mark%20Zuckerberg%20pointing.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bc1bc46fcb546d2d4b6aa2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMeta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%3Cp%3EBrendan%20Smialowski%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20existing%20for-profit%20parts%20of%20OpenAI%20have%20already%20raised%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20pursuit%20of%20%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3EArtificial%20General%20Intelligence%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20AGI%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhich%20the%20startup%20defines%20as%20systems%20that%20outperform%20humans%20at%20most%20economically%20valuable%20work.%20This%20has%20raised%20hackles%20among%20some%20consumer%20advocates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublic%20Citizen%2C%20a%20consumer%20watchdog%2C%20has%20repeatedly%20assailed%20the%20AI%20startup%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20betraying%20its%20nonprofit%20mission.%20%26quot%3BThe%20nonprofit%20board%20has%20behaved%20as%20a%20subordinate%20to%20the%20for-profit%2C%20and%20has%20done%20nothing%20that%20evidences%20any%20commitment%20to%20the%20nonprofit%20mission%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Robert%20Weissman%2C%20the%20co-president%20of%20Public%20Citizen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20solution%20is%20to%20forcibly%20dissolve%20the%20nonprofit%20and%20auction%20off%20its%20assets%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20a%20new%20independent%20charity%20not%20linked%20to%20the%20current%20OpenAI%20board%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFacebook%20parent%20company%20Meta%20raised%20similar%20concerns%2C%20writing%20to%20the%20California%20Attorney%20General%20Rob%20Bonta%20in%20December%20to%20ask%20him%20to%20step%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTaking%20advantage%20of%20this%20non-profit%20status%2C%20OpenAI%20raised%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20capital%20from%20investors%20to%20further%20its%20purported%20mission%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20OpenAI%20wants%20to%20change%20its%20status%20while%20retaining%20all%20of%20the%20benefits%20that%20enabled%20it%20to%20reach%20the%20point%20it%20has%20today.%20That%20is%20wrong.%20OpenAI%20should%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20flout%20the%20law%20by%20taking%20and%20reappropriating%20assets%20it%20built%20as%20a%20charity%20and%20using%20them%20for%20potentially%20enormous%20private%20gains.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20January%2C%20a%20group%20of%2025%20charities%2C%20including%20one%20started%20by%20eBay%20founder%20Pierre%20Omidyar%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20piled%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20coalition%20wrote%20to%20the%20California%20AG%3Cstrong%3E%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsff.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F01%2FCharitable-coalition-letter-on-OpenAI-conversion-1-29-25.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eurging%20him%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bto%20take%20prompt%20legal%20action%20to%20ensure%20that%20OpenAI's%20assets%20are%20not%20illegally%20diverted%20for%20private%20gain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e4711840-e174-4004-83f9-2a10bdb00257%5C%22%3EDubious%20legal%20justifications%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERose%20Chan-Loui%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20UCLA%20specializing%20in%20non-profit%20and%20philanthropy%20law%2C%20is%20dubious%20of%20the%20legal%20justifications%20for%20OpenAI's%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20proposed%20changes%20would%20amount%20to%20a%20change%20in%20purpose%20for%20OpenAI's%20current%20non-profit.%20To%20do%20that%20under%20Delaware%20law%2C%20requires%20one%20of%20four%20criteria%20to%20be%20met%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIs%20the%20charity's%20original%20purpose%20now%20illegal%20to%20fulfill%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHas%20the%20mission%20become%20impossible%20to%20fulfill%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIs%20it%20now%20impracticable%20to%20fulfill%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOr%20too%20wasteful%20to%20fulfill.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20think%20any%20of%20those%20apply%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Chan-Loui%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20keep%20going%20back%20to%20%E2%80%94%20your%20purpose%20is%20not%20to%20be%20first%20in%20the%20race%20to%20AGI.%20Your%20purpose%20is%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20AGI%20is%20to%20protect%2C%20and%20ensure%20safe%20development%20of%20AGI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223655b8d9-8646-4350-b94d-be7eb6fd87d6%5C%22%3EThe%20lesson%20of%20other%20nonprofits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20existing%20structure%20%E2%80%94%20a%20non-profit%20that%20controls%20a%20for-profit%20subsidiary%20%E2%80%94%20is%20unusual%2C%20but%20by%20no%20means%20unheard%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Mozilla%20Foundation%2C%20for%20example%2C%20owns%20a%20tech%20company%2C%20Mozilla%20Corporation%2C%20that%20produces%20the%20Firefox%20internet%20browser.%20%26quot%3BNon-profit%20organizations%20can%20not%20only%20coexist%20with%20commercial%20enterprises%20but%20also%20challenge%20them%20to%20do%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Mozilla%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BNon-profit%20commitments%20provide%20the%20kind%20of%20public%20interest%20compass%20we%20don't%20see%20enough%20of%20in%20tech.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20parallel%20comes%20from%20the%20healthcare%20sector.%20In%20the%201990s%2C%20in%20the%20face%20of%20mounting%20financial%20pressure%2C%20the%20Blue%20Cross%20Blue%20Shield%20Association%20allowed%20its%20affiliated%20nonprofit%20plan%20organizations%20to%20transition%20to%20for-profit%20businesses.%20Many%20subsequently%20did%20so%2C%20to%20the%20chagrin%20of%20some.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20mission%20of%20the%20non-profit%20in%20most%20Blue%20Cross%20Blue%20Shield%20plans%20was%20to%20provide%20affordable%2C%20accessible%20health%20care%20to%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Consumers%20Union%20attorney%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2010%2F03%2F18%2F124807720%2Fdid-blue-cross-mission-stray-when-plans-became-for-profit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20NPR%20in%202010%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20now%20the%20mission%20is%20to%20make%20money%20for%20stockholders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20substantial%20threat%20to%20OpenAI's%20plans%20though%2C%20might%20not%20be%20Elon%20Musk%20or%20other%20critics.%20The%20California%20and%20Delaware%20Attorneys%20General%20are%20both%20making%20inquiries%20into%20the%20specifics%20of%20the%20transition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20current%20beneficiaries%20of%20OpenAI%20have%20an%20interest%20in%20ensuring%20that%20charitable%20assets%20are%20not%20transferred%20to%20private%20interests%20without%20due%20consideration%2C%26quot%3B%20Delaware%20AG%20Kathleen%20Jennings%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAGs%20have%20meaningful%20legal%20powers%20to%20get%20involved.%20In%202002%2C%20Pennsylvania's%20Attorney%20General%20intervened%20in%20a%20planned%20deal%20by%20the%20non-profit%20foundation%20that%20controls%20the%20for-profit%20Hershey%20chocolate%20brand%20to%20sell%20its%20assets%20to%20Wrigley%20for%20%2412%20billion%2C%20citing%20the%20potential%20harm%20to%20the%20town%20of%20Hershey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sale%20was%20ultimately%20called%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-elon-musk-sam-altman-for-profit-conversion-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740477602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67acfec97bb3f854015cb021%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-elon-musk-sam-altman-for-profit-conversion-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Meta%2C%20AI%20entrepreneurs%2C%20academics%2C%20and%20other%20charities%20and%20activists%20are%20criticizing%20the%20startup's%20plan%20to%20shed%20its%20ties%20to%20its%20non-profit%20parent.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rprice%40insider.com%20(Rob%20Price)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A127%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-elon-musk-sam-altman-for-profit-conversion-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20former%20Fed%20economist%20braces%20for%20slowed%20US%20growth%20and%20shares%20the%203%20biggest%20risks%20for%20markets%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226236%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20bill%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67059ee2198738e3a70f3500%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223448%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3Eshowing%20former%20president%20Washington%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EInvestors'%20optimism%20for%202025%20is%20waning%20as%20market%20risks%20increase%2C%20impacting%20stocks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEconomic%20concerns%2C%20including%20inflation%20and%20tariffs%2C%20are%20top%20risks%20for%20corporate%20leaders.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGeopolitical%20risks%20and%20federal%20disruptions%20could%20further%20strain%20the%20US%20economic%20outlook.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors'%20high%20hopes%20coming%20into%202025%20are%20slowly%20being%20dashed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20optimism%20that%20was%20priced%20into%20the%20market%20is%20starting%20to%20reverse%20course.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26amp%3Bp_500%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500's%3C%2Fa%3E%20pullback%20last%20week%20could%20indicate%20that%20investors%20are%20reducing%20their%20risk%20appetite%2C%20said%20Julia%20Coronado%2C%20president%20of%20the%20research%20firm%20Macropolicy%20Perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20three%20stock-market%20indexes%20closed%20down%20on%20Friday%20amid%20flashing%20signs%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-today-dow-worst-day-economic-data-consumer-sentiment-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslowdown%20in%20US%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20US%20Composite%20Flash%20PMI%20Output%20Index%2C%20which%20measures%20monthly%20changes%20in%20goods%20and%20services%2C%20neared%20contraction%20territory%20in%20February%20and%20hit%20a%2017-month%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumer%20spending%2C%20the%20economy's%20main%20driver%2C%20may%20also%20be%20at%20risk.%20The%20University%20of%20Michigan%20Surveys%20of%20Consumers%20posted%20on%20Friday%20showed%20sentiment%20fell%20for%20the%20second%20consecutive%20month%20by%20nearly%2010%25%20from%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20comes%20as%20a%20surprise%20to%20corporate%20insiders.%20A%20recent%20survey%20by%20Protiviti%20and%20North%20Carolina%20State%20University%2C%20which%20polled%201%2C215%20board%20members%20and%20C-suite%20executives%20about%20their%20biggest%20concerns%2C%20put%20economic%20conditions%2C%20including%20inflationary%20pressures%2C%20as%20the%20top%20risk%20in%20their%20near-%20and%20long-term%20outlooks.%20It%20means%20that%20corporate%20activity%2C%20and%20specifically%20spending%2C%20is%20teetering%20on%20clarity%20around%20tariffs.%20And%20so%2C%20the%20PMI's%20contraction%20is%20just%20an%20uncertainty%20tax%2C%20Coronado%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTariffs%20in%20and%20of%20themselves%20aren't%20a%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20tell%20me%20what%20the%20tariff%20is%2C%20then%20I%20can%20factor%20that%20into%20my%20supply%20chain%20management%2C%20my%20cost%20structures%2C%20my%20pricing%20strategy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20former%20economist%20for%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Board%2C%20she%20believes%20it%20will%20take%20further%20policy%20clarity%20from%20Washington%20before%20spending%20can%20resume.%20So%20far%2C%20only%20a%2010%25%20tariff%20against%20imports%20from%20China%20has%20been%20implemented.%20Everything%20else%20is%20still%20hanging%20in%20the%20mix%2C%20including%20the%20possibility%20of%20counter-tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b3a51656-8aa3-4b14-9f21-6b43c4f81a13%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESentiment%20and%20outlook%20shifts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMarkets%20came%20into%20the%20year%20sanguine%2C%20she%20said.%20The%20response%20to%20the%20election%20was%20positive.%20Expectations%20were%20focused%20on%20growth%20elements%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-pay-in-taxes-trump-tax-bill-expiring-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etax%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-us-stock-market-underperforming-europe-international-trump-america-first-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ederegulation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20we%20are%20getting%20hit%20with%20more%20negative%20or%20disruptive%20parts%20of%20policy%20first%2C%20like%20immigration%20reforms%20that%20tighten%20labor%20supply%2C%20tariffs%2C%20and%20a%20wave%20of%20government%20job%20cuts%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20any%20positive%20impacts%20of%20deregulation%20are%20harder%20to%20calibrate%20into%20the%20economy%20and%20will%20take%20a%20long%20time%20to%20reflect.%20It%20will%20also%20take%20more%20time%20to%20get%20tax%20cuts%20or%20see%20their%20benefits%2C%20she%20noted.%20All%20this%20is%20gradually%20making%20sentiment%20more%20negative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20couple%20of%20years%20featured%20better-than-expected%20cooling%20on%20inflation%20alongside%20a%20resilient%20economy.%20The%20Fed's%20preferred%20measure%20of%20inflation%2C%20core%20personal%20consumption%20expenditures%2C%20which%20excludes%20volatile%20food%20and%20energy%20prices%2C%20hovered%20at%202.8%25%20at%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year.%20Before%20the%20threat%20of%20tariffs%2C%20Coronado%20was%20forecasting%20continued%20progress%20toward%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20target.%20But%20that's%20now%20changed.%20She%20expects%20inflation%20to%20stall%20and%20remain%20close%20to%203%25%20instead%20of%20cooling%20down%2C%20with%20risk%20to%20the%20upside%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year%20if%20more%20tariffs%20begin%20to%20trickle%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20saw%20last%20time%20we%20did%20a%20trade%20war%20under%20Trump's%20first%20administration%20is%20it%20kind%20of%20hit%20the%20global%20manufacturing%20sector%20and%20took%20the%20sector%20into%20recession%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fed%2C%20because%20inflation%20was%20low%20at%20the%20time%2C%20was%20able%20to%20cut%20rates%20and%20soften%20the%20blow.%20We%20don't%20think%20that's%20the%20case%20this%20time%20because%20inflation%20is%20above%20their%20target.%20So%20they%20won't%20be%20cutting%20rates%20anytime%20soon.%20And%20you%20will%20see%20the%20pass-through%20impact%20of%20some%20of%20these%20policies%20on%20growth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20doesn't%20expect%20any%20rate%20cuts%20until%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%2C%20why%20do%20we%20have%20the%20Fed%20cutting%20at%20all%20is%20a%20good%20question.%20And%20that%20comes%20down%20to%3A%20we%20do%20expect%20that%20growth%20will%20cool%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20forecast%20for%20US%20GDP%20is%202.5%25%20for%20the%20early%20part%20of%20the%20year%20but%20slowing%20to%201%25%20by%20the%20fourth%20quarter.%20The%20job%20market%20is%20also%20expected%20to%20slow%20down%2C%20going%20from%20an%20average%20of%20175%2C000%20jobs%20created%20monthly%20to%20below%20100%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20indication%20that%20fear%20is%20spreading%20through%20markets%20is%20a%20widening%20of%20credit%20spreads%20as%20investors%20demand%20higher%20yields%20for%20taking%20on%20more%20risk%20of%20default%2C%20which%20is%20what%20Coronado%20will%20be%20watching%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220e1bc480-4f9a-40e6-b5d6-e771804d8ce3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBiggest%20risks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20risk%20of%20a%20recession%20is%20always%20there.%20In%20any%20given%20year%2C%20it%20sits%20at%20a%2020%25%20chance%2C%20but%20Coronado%20has%20set%20a%2035%25%20chance%20of%20a%20recession%20over%20the%20next%2012%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHer%20biggest%20fear%20is%20geopolitical%20risks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20and%20shifts%20in%20alliances%20between%20countries.%20On%20the%20pro%20side%2C%20conflict%20would%20be%20a%20positive%20for%20the%20defense%20sector.%20On%20the%20cons%20side%2C%20it%20would%20negatively%20affect%20the%20European%20economy.%20As%20for%20Mexico%20and%20Canada%20relations%2C%20if%20tariffs%20are%20implemented%2C%20it%20would%20negatively%20hit%20the%20auto%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHer%20second%20concern%20is%20disruptions%20to%20the%20federal%20payments%20system%20and%20contracts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20which%20are%20being%20witnessed%20amid%20the%20DOGE%20shake-ups%20that%20are%20laying%20off%20federal%20workers%20and%20trying%20to%20cut%20down%20spending.%20This%20will%20especially%20hit%20sectors%20such%20as%20renewable%20energy%2C%20agricultural%20firms%2C%20and%20even%20payments%20to%20hospitals%20that%20are%20being%20interrupted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20macroeconomist%2C%20I%20tend%20to%20think%20that%20one%20of%20the%20ingredients%20to%20US%20exceptionalism%20is%20stability%20and%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20Coronado%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we've%20seen%20a%20lot%20of%20disruptive%20actions%20that%20directly%20involve%20payment%20systems%20and%20being%20a%20person%20that's%20in%20markets%20and%20appreciates%20liquidity%20and%20efficiency%20of%20operations%2C%20it%20worries%20me%20to%20see%20chaotic%20intervention.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAs%20for%20AI%20stocks%2C%20there's%20too%20much%20speculative%20excess%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20priced%20into%20their%20valuations%2C%20she%20noted.%20Even%20big%20winners%20like%20Nvidia%2C%20with%20wide%20profit%20margins%2C%20are%20expected%20to%20see%20a%20slowdown%20in%20growth%20as%20the%20company%20matures%20and%20competition%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI's%20impact%20on%20productivity%20is%20real%20and%20will%20be%20a%20positive%20tailwind.%20Still%2C%20for%20now%2C%20markets%20may%20have%20gotten%20ahead%20of%20themselves%20as%20they%20bet%20on%20what%20she%20believes%20is%20unsustainable%20valuations.%20This%20suggests%20that%20the%20resilience%20of%20Big%20Tech's%20ability%20to%20carry%20the%20market%20through%20uncertainty%20will%20be%20tested%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it's%20not%20all%20doom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUS%20companies%20just%20proved%20themselves%20to%20be%20very%20resilient%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20uncertain%20developments%20during%20and%20after%20the%20pandemic%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20wouldn't%20count%20them%20out.%20There%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20battle-tested%20risk%20managers%20across%20many%20sectors.%20They're%20going%20to%20definitely%20have%20a%20busy%20year%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20it's%20automatically%20going%20to%20be%20the%20worst%20outcome%20that%20manifests%20itself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-former-fed-economist-3-biggest-risks-markets-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740477602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bcaf044e7cbbbe3dc4586d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-former-fed-economist-3-biggest-risks-markets-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22We%20are%20getting%20hit%20with%20all%20the%20bad%20before%20the%20good%2C%20said%20Julia%20Coronado.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmaidan%40businessinsider.com%20(Laila%20Maidan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-former-fed-economist-3-biggest-risks-markets-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Australian%20Docu-Soap%20%E2%80%98Billion%20Dollar%20Playground%E2%80%99%20Acquired%20by%20Several%20Major%20Broadcasters%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740477600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FBillion-Dollar-Playground-1.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236319272%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fox%20Ent.%20Global%2C%20Fox%20Ent.%E2%80%99s%20worldwide%20content%20sales%20division%2C%20has%20secured%20key%20international%20pre-sales%20for%20Foxtel%E2%80%99s%20Australian%20docu-soap%20%E2%80%9CBillion%20Dollar%20Playground%2C%E2%80%9D%20with%20major%20broadcasters%20acquiring%20the%20series%20for%20their%20local%20audiences.%20Under%20these%20deals%2C%20the%20series%2C%20produced%20by%20Ronde%20Media%2C%20will%